From the developed area drive north on Highway 67 to the Cape Royal Road.  Turn right and travel east on the Cape Royal road to the Point Imperial "Y" and turn right.  Continuing on the Cape Royal Road travel south 4.1 miles to the E5/E6 road on the west (right) side of the road. Turn south (right) onto E5/E6 and travel 1.8 miles from the gate, staying right where E5 splits to the west, to reach the reference stake.    The reference stake is on the west (right) side of the road in a small clearing near the base of a pole-sized aspen. The reference stake is 1.0 miles from the E5-E6 jct.  Ref. stake UTMs: 0413024e, 4006626n    From the reference stake hike 15 chains at 270 deg. to reach the plot located at the bottom of a small drainage.    Cat Scratch fever plot

Drive on the Cape Royal Road 4.1 miles past the junction with Point Imperial, the Y. Turn right onto the E-4 road and travel 0.7 miles to the reference stake on the west (right) side of the road. The reference stake is in a small opening surrounded by white firs. The reference stake is also located across the road from a large PIPO with orange diamond markers on both sides of the tree. From the stake hike ~ 19-20 chains at 315 degrees to reach the plot origin.     Reference stake UTMs: 410908e, 4009237n

SampleEventComment: From FMH 1029 Lots of brush in this plot; may consider throwing it out due to fire effects?? Tonja and Kara, 8/99.

SampleEventTeam: Brannfors, Murdoch, Talbert x2, Pasotti, McClure

Directions: From the "Y" intersection of the Cape Royal and Pt. Imperial Roads, travel south (right) 4.1 miles to the E4 Road.  Go south on E4 road 1.3 mile.  The reference stake is on the west (right) side of the road at the base of a 50-60 centimeter DBH PIPO approximately 5 meters off the road.  PIPO has mistletoe brooms and is quite charred along its trunk.  Ref. stake UTMs: E 0410603, N 4008408     From the reference stake, hike due west at 270 for ~17 chains to plot origin.    NOTE:  The reference stake was moved ~0.1 miles south and across the road from the original stake.  Therefore, compass & chain methodology may not result in arriving exactly at the plot.      PLOTASAUR PLOT/ LAND O THE BIG PIPOS/ SANTA CLAUS PLOT

SampleEventTeam: McCLURE, BRANNFORS, MARSHALL,  DANG,  MURDOCH, VAUGHAN, BANWELL

Directions: From the developed area drive north on Highway 67 to the Cape Royal Road.  Turn right and travel east on the Cape Royal road to the Point Imperial "Y" and turn right. Continuing on the Cape Royal Road travel south (right) 4.1 miles to the E5/E6 road on the west (right) side of the road. Turn south (right) onto the E5/E6 and drive a total of 1.1 miles from the gate making sure to keep west (right) where the E5 and E6 diverge. The reference stake will be 0.35 miles from the E5-E6 junction. The reference stake is on the west side of the road at the base of a POTR and ABCO growing as twins.  Ref. stake UTMs: 0411074e, 4007102n.    From the ref. stake, hike 35-40 chains due west at 270o to plot origin.       NOTE:  Beware of lenscap!

SampleEventTeam: Brannfors, Jenkins, Worthington, Straus, Mahood, Maughan, Garmoe, Harper

Directions: From the Cape Royal/Pt. Imperial Y junction drive 4.1 miles down the Cape Royal Road to the E-4 road. Turn right onto the E-4 and drive 2.2 miles to reach the reference stake on the west (right) side of the road on the uphill side of a small drainage, just past a rocky area in the road and a large stump on the right.  It's in front of a smaller overstory PIPO and just before a dandy parking area.  Ref. stake UTMs:  0411074 E, 4007102 N.    From the reference stake hike 7 chains at 270o to reach the plot origin.  The hike is mostly level, and there is a sinkhole immediately west of the plot.

SampleEventTeam: H. Gillespie, J. Peach, M. J. Geldert

Directions: From the developed area drive north on Highway 67 to the Cape Royal Road.  Turn right and travel east on the Cape Royal road to the Point Imperial "Y" and turn right.  Continuing on the Cape Royal Road travel south 4.1 miles to the E5/E6 road on the west (right) side of the road. Turn south (right) onto the E5/E6 and drive to where the E5 and E6 diverge.  Park here to find the reference stake at the base of a large PIPO festooned with an orange road marker in the "Y" between the two roads.  Ref. stake UTMs: 0413681e, 4008135n.    From the reference stake hike 45 chains at 270o to reach the plot origin.  En route you will walk through several areas torched out during the Vista Fire.  At least for the near future, this means you will also encounter a plethora of locust, chenopodium, cirsium, and cleverly hidden downed 1000 hrs in these openings.  It would be advisable to detour south around these unless you enjoy having flashbacks to Nam.  Eventually you may pass a sinkhole and wind up on an open ponderosa bench with manzanita in abundance.  The bench slopes away to the WSW, and the plot can be found just down the slope, where mixed conifer makes an appearance again and there is a pocket of dead trees.    Alternately, you could use the GPS to drive down E5 to find the point nearest to the plot and navigate onward from there.

Take Cape Royal Road 0.4 miles south past the Vista Encantada entrance to reach the reference stake.    The reference stake is on the south (right) side of the road, 5-6 chains east of a road sign on the north side of the road, and partly hidden in a small clump of rocks a few meters off the road side. There is a small manzanita bush growing near the rocks. Ref. stake UTMs: 0412745e, 4009496n.    From ref. stake hike 22-25 chains at 225o to the plot origin.  You will go downhill to the drainage bottom and a very short distance up the other side of the drainage.      WHAT A MESS PLOT!

SampleEventTeam: M.J. Geldert, H. Gillespie, J. Peach

Directions: Drive Cape Royal Road 4.1 miles past the junction with Pt. Imperial Road to the E4 road.  Turn right onto E4 and proceed south 0.45 miles to reach the reference stake.    The reference stake is now at the base of an 86 centimeter DBH PIPO on the east (left) side of the road, ascending a small incline (stake moved and retagged on 08/25/99).   Ref. stake UTMs 0411175e,  4009387n.    From the reference stake, hike 26 chains at 135o to reach the plot origin.  You will drop into a small drainage, then head slightly uphill/sidehill before reaching the plot on top of a subdued bench.  About halfway, you will cross an old fireline.  Just east of the plot is a small clearing.

From the Developed Area, drive Hwy 67 north to the jct with the W1a Range Road across from the turnoff to Lindbergh Hill.  Turn south onto the W1a rd and travel 1.3 miles to the crest of a small rise for a good parking spot.  Barely a chain further along and slightly downhill from the hilltop is a white fir with a metal pole attached to its south side, supporting a wooden snowmobile route sign with an orange arrow in a yellow square on the east (left) side of the road.  The reference tag is affixed to this metal pole.  Ref. tag UTMs:  0402923e, 4014462 n.    Alternately, turn off Hwy 67 at the W1 rd and drive 0.9 miles to the jct with the W1a rd.  Turn north (right) onto the W1a rd and travel 3.5 miles to reach the ref. tag and feature on the east (right) side of the road.    From the reference tag hike ~23 chains at 85 up and over a small hill to reach the plot origin in a very subtle saddle.

Directions: Drive Hwy 67 north 4.3 miles past the park entrance station and turn left at Forest Service road 22 before the Kaibab Lodge.  Travel 2.1 miles on 22, then turn left at the stop sign onto FS 270.  Go 2.3 miles on 270 (stay left at 0.8 miles), to reach the junction with FS 223.  Stay straight on 270 for 1.0 more miles (follow the powerlines at any junctions), then turn right onto signed road 270G.  Stay on 270G for 2.0 miles to reach the reference stake on the south (left) side of the road at the base of a funky ABCO (bark looks PSME, needles look ABLA).  There is a large PIPO and a good parking space just across the road.  The "2" on the tag is difficult to read.  Ref. stake UTMs: 395543e, 4023466n.    From ref. stake, walk ~7 chains at 197o to reach the plot origin.

Drive ~5 mi. north of the North Rim Entrance Station on Hwy 67 and turn right on Forest Service Road 611 (just south of Kaibab Lodge, and directly across from FS 22).  Continue on this road 1.3 mi. to the junction with FS road 610 and turn right onto 610.  Drive ~12.0 mi. on the main 610 road to reach the old Point Imperial Road/Trail trailhead.  It will be easiest to park just down the road at the Saddle Mountain/Nankoweap Trailhead and hike back up the road.    Hike south on the old Pt. Imperial Road/Trail for ~50 chains to a drainage and the reference stake on the west (right) side of the trail.  The ref. stake is behind a broken aspen with a split ~7 off the ground.  Ref. stake UTMs:  0410526e, 4016911n.    From the ref. stake hike down the drainage bottom ~9 chains at 220 to reach the plot origin.

Drive Hwy 67 north 4.3 miles past the park entrance station and turn left at Forest Service road 22 before the Kaibab Lodge.  Travel 2.1 miles on 22, then turn left at the stop sign onto FS 270.  Go 2.3 miles on 270 (stay left at 0.8 miles), to reach the junction with FS 223.  Stay straight on 270 for 1.0 more miles (follow the powerlines at any junctions), then turn right onto signed road 270G.  Stay on 270G for 2.2 miles to reach the reference stake on the south (left) side of the road near the base of a seedling ABCO next to 3 large pole-sized aspen and a similarly-sized dead PIEN.  This is just a tad less than 0.2 mi. past the PIEN 02 ref stake.  You will start to descend a hill just before reaching the stake.  The stake is approximately 2 m from the road, across the road from a lone overstory ABCO. Ref. stake UTMs: 0395257e, 4023499n.    Hike ~5.5 chains at 190o from the ref. stake to reach the plot origin.

Drive Hwy 67 to N Rim Entrance Station.  Turn east onto the road across from the entrance station, and drive left past the cabin until you reach the usually locked gate.  From the gate, drive 1.3 mi. up the N Rim Entrance Tower rd. to reach the end of the road and the ref. tag dangling from the lookout tower.  Dont forget to look for smoke and feel the aura of Edward Abbey while youre there.  Ref. tag UTMs (in case you cant find the tower):  401112 E, 4021174 N.    From the tower, hike ~15-16 chains at 251o to reach the plot origin.  The plot is located on a WSW facing slope.      Lookout/Abbey plot!

Directions: Option 1: Take the W1 to the W4.  From the junction drive north on the W4 for 2.65 miles to a sharp corner just before the Kanabownits cabin.  Option 2: Drive in on the forest to the W4, to the Kanabownits Y. Drive 5.9 miles south from the junction to a sharp corner just after the Kanabownits cabin.  There is an old road that runs ENE from this corner. The old road is overgrown with downed trees, but still visible. The reference stake is located at the base of a PIPO on the east side of the road, E 0391132, N 4016295.    To get to the plot origin from the reference stake, hike up the old road and (using the GPS), break away to continue up a drainage.      THE SNOW IN SEPTEMBER PLOT

Follow W1 straightaway for 1.9 mi to Reference Stake. Reference Stake on right side of road at base of "twin" JUOS & PIED. Good clearing and parking area immediately after, before big descent.

Drive 0.2 miles and turn left on Power line Road.  Drive 0.5 miles to reference stake on the right side of the road, next to the 3C-205 power line pole.
